title.narrative: Enhancing Nigeria's Response to HIV/AIDS - Procurement of Services

description.narrative: This activity (Enhancing Nigeria's Response to HIV/AIDS - Procurement of Services) is a component of Enhancing Nigeria's Response to HIV/AIDS reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £53,947,625. This component benefits Nigeria, and works in the following sector(s): Health policy and administrative management, Health education, Family planning, STD control including HIV/AIDS. , with the following implementing partners: Mott MacDonald Limited, Oxford Policy Management. The start date is 01-10-2008 and the end date is 31-12-2016.
